\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Synthetic respondent scores across seven validated clinical instruments. Each panel shows the mean score (95\% CI) for clinically relevant diagnostic groups and an averaged clinical control group (all nontarget diagnoses) at three severity levels (light: mild; medium: moderate; dark: severe). Dashed lines indicate published clinical cutoff scores: PHQ-9 $\geq $ 10; GAD-7 $\geq $ 10; OCI-R $\geq $ 21; PCL-5 $\geq $ 33; MDQ $\geq $ 7; PQ-16 $\geq $ 6; EDE-Q $\geq $ 2.3. EDE-Q scores reflect the global mean (0--6 scale); all other instruments use summed totals. $n = 2106$ synthetic personas generated by Google Gemini 2.0 Flash.}}{10}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:1}{{1}{10}{Synthetic respondent scores across seven validated clinical instruments. Each panel shows the mean score (95\% CI) for clinically relevant diagnostic groups and an averaged clinical control group (all nontarget diagnoses) at three severity levels (light: mild; medium: moderate; dark: severe). Dashed lines indicate published clinical cutoff scores: PHQ-9 $\geq $ 10; GAD-7 $\geq $ 10; OCI-R $\geq $ 21; PCL-5 $\geq $ 33; MDQ $\geq $ 7; PQ-16 $\geq $ 6; EDE-Q $\geq $ 2.3. EDE-Q scores reflect the global mean (0--6 scale); all other instruments use summed totals. $n = 2106$ synthetic personas generated by Google Gemini 2.0 Flash}{figure.1}{}}
